Program: Discovery
Title: Sexual Nature 2/3
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p0141tgt
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 17 Feb 2013
Sex is one of Nature’s great forces of change. Yet it is one of life’s great mysteries. Adam Rutherford investigates how and why living things first invented sex about 1.5 billion years ago. He begins by exploring why so many animals and plants have carried on doing it, given that sex has some big disadvantages compared to asexual reproduction. Show less